ENTRY            F1190   20260116   20260508   20260508       F108
SUBENT        F1190001   20260116   20260508   20260508       F108
BIB                  9         19
TITLE      Interfering resonances in the 19F(alpha,p)22Ne reaction
AUTHOR     (J.Kuperus)
INSTITUTE  (2NEDUTR)
REFERENCE  (J,PHY,31,1603,1965)
           #doi:10.1016/0031-8914(65)90129-1
FACILITY   (VDG,2NEDUTR) The 3 MV Van de Graaff generator was used
DETECTOR   (SIBAR) Eight surface barrier detectors situated at
           laboratory angles of 40, 55, 70, 87, 105, 120, 140 and
           172 degrees with respect to the incoming beam were
           used.
SAMPLE     Targets of SrF2 evaporated on a solid backing were
           used. Targets with the thicknesses of 10 ug/cm2 were
           used for the energy less than 2300 keV and of
           20 ug/cm2 for the energy more than 2300 keV.
ERR-ANALYS (ERR-1) The target deterioration is the main reason
           of the uncertainty in yields and strengths.
HISTORY    (20130702C)
           (20260116U) SD: Corrections in all Subents.
           DATA-ERR -> ERR-1.
ENDBIB              19
COMMON               2          3
ANG        ERR-1
ADEG       PER-CENT
       120.        40.
ENDCOMMON            3
ENDSUBENT           26
SUBENT        F1190002   20260116   20260508   20260508       F108
BIB                  3          5
